# ApparenceKit Supabase Boilerplate — Setup Roadmap

**Last Updated:** March 20, 2026

This guide walks you through setting up a new app from this boilerplate.

---

## Prerequisites

- Flutter SDK (stable channel, Dart SDK ^3.11.0)
- A Supabase account (https://supabase.com) OR local Supabase via Docker
- A Firebase account (for push notifications and current auth — migration to Supabase auth is planned)
- Node.js + npm (for Firebase CLI)
- Git

---

## Step 1: Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/digisurfsome/apparence-kit-supabase.git my-app
cd my-app
```

---

## Step 2: Install Flutter Dependencies

```bash
flutter pub get
```

---

## Step 3: Run Code Generation

The project uses `freezed`, `json_serializable`, and `riverpod_generator`. Generated files (`.g.dart`, `.freezed.dart`) are NOT committed to git.

```bash
dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs
```

---

## Step 4: Create a Supabase Project

### Option A: Supabase Cloud

1. Go to https://supabase.com/dashboard
2. Click "New Project"
3. Note your **Project URL** and **Anon Key** from Settings > API

### Option B: Local Supabase (Docker)

```bash
# Install Supabase CLI
npm install -g supabase

# Start local Supabase
supabase start

# Note the API URL and anon key from the output
```

---

## Step 5: Run Supabase Migrations

Apply the SQL migrations that create the tables the app expects:

```bash
# If using Supabase CLI with a linked project:
supabase db push

# Or apply manually via the Supabase SQL Editor:
# Run each file in supabase/migrations/ in order
```

Tables created:
- `users` — user profiles
- `subscriptions` — user subscriptions
- `notifications` — push notifications
- `feature_requests` — feature request board
- `feature_votes` — votes on feature requests
- `user_feature_requests` — user-submitted feature requests
- `user_infos` — key-value user metadata (onboarding answers)

All tables include Row Level Security (RLS) policies.

---

## Step 6: Set Up Firebase (for Push Notifications)

The current codebase uses Firebase for auth and notifications. Firebase setup is required until the Supabase auth migration is complete.

```bash
# Install Firebase CLI
npm install -g firebase-tools

# Login
firebase login

# Install FlutterFire CLI
dart pub global activate flutterfire_cli

# Configure Firebase for your project
flutterfire configure --project=YOUR_PROJECT_ID

# Generate dev config
flutterfire configure --project=YOUR_PROJECT_ID --out lib/firebase_options_dev.dart
```

---

## Step 7: Set Environment Variables

The app reads configuration from Dart environment variables (compile-time constants via `--dart-define`).

Required variables:
```bash
# Backend / Supabase
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
BACKEND_URL=https://your-api-url.com  # or leave empty if using Supabase directly

# Environment
ENV=dev  # or 'prod'

# RevenueCat (optional, for in-app purchases)
RC_ANDROID_API_KEY=your-android-key
RC_IOS_API_KEY=your-ios-key

# Analytics (optional)
MIXPANEL_TOKEN=your-mixpanel-token

# Error reporting (prod only)
SENTRY_DSN=your-sentry-dsn

# App Store (for rating prompts)
APP_STORE_ID=your-app-store-id
```

Run the app with environment variables:
```bash
flutter run --dart-define=ENV=dev --dart-define=BACKEND_URL=https://your-url.com
```

---

## Step 8: Replace Template-Specific Values

### App Name
Replace in ALL of these locations:
- `pubspec.yaml` — `name:` field
- `web/index.html:32` — `<title>`
- `web/index.html:26` — `apple-mobile-web-app-title`
- `web/manifest.json:2-3` — `name` and `short_name`
- `android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml:11` — `android:label`
- `lib/modules/notifications/api/local_notifier.dart:24` — `kAppName`
- `lib/main.dart:126` — MaterialApp `title`

### Bundle ID / Application ID
Replace `com.yourcompany.template` in:
- `android/app/build.gradle.kts` — `namespace` and `applicationId`
- `android/app/src/main/kotlin/com/yourcompany/template/MainActivity.kt` — package declaration + rename directory
- iOS: Xcode project settings

You can use the `change_app_package_name` dev dependency:
```bash
dart run change_app_package_name:main com.yourcompany.yourapp
```

### Facebook SDK (if using Facebook events/login)
- `android/app/src/main/res/values/strings.xml:3-4` — Replace placeholder `000000000000` with your Facebook App ID and Client Token

### Terms & Privacy URLs
- `lib/environments.dart:23-24` — Set `kTermsUrl` and `kPrivacyUrl`

### Firebase Region
- `lib/core/data/api/user_api.dart:14` — Change `_kFirebaseRegion` to match your project
- `lib/modules/authentication/api/authentication_api.dart:18` — Same

---

## Step 9: Update kit_setup.json

Edit `kit_setup.json` to reflect your actual configuration (app name, bundle ID, providers, etc.).

---

## Step 10: Run the App

```bash
# Debug mode
flutter run

# Or with environment variables
flutter run --dart-define=ENV=dev --dart-define=BACKEND_URL=https://your-url.com
```

---

## Step 11: Run Tests

```bash
flutter test
```

---

## Step 12: Run Analysis

```bash
flutter analyze lib test
```

